{"title_page": "Michael Farthofer", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic sailor from Austria}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Michael Farthofer<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" />\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| native_name    = \n| birth_name     =  \n| fullname       = \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{AUT}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1955|6|8|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Vancouver]], {{CAN}}\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.74|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = \n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 27 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Michael Farthofer''' (born 8 June 1955) is a sailor from [[Austria]], who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1984 Summer Olympics]] in [[Los Angeles]], [[United States]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]]. With crew members [[Christian Holler]] and [[Richard Holler]] they took the 15th place.<ref name=\"OS1984\" />\n{{Footer Austrian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fa/michael-farthofer-1.html\n                                  |title      = Michael Farthofer Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n                                  |accessdate = 27 February 2020 \n                                  |url-status = live\n                                  |df=dmy \n                                }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS1984>{{cite web\n                        | url        = https://digital.la84.org/digital/collection/p17103coll8/id/45225/rec/52\n    